From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 05:15:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Force preferred DualSense mono retargets.

Controller hotplug generates Pulse events before the refreshed render device
list is committed. A live controller-speaker stream can observe those early
events, decide that it is still on the current sink, and update its generation
bookkeeping while the old sink is still visible. When the replacement sink is
then added, a generation-only skip can leave that stream bound to the old
controller until the same model is unplugged and replugged again.

When pulse_get_endpoint_ids() has an exact newly-added DualSense speaker sink,
run the retarget against that preferred sink regardless of the cached generation
state. Keep the generation skip for generic write-time fallback retargets.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 99999999999..aaaaaaaaaaa 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -2498,9 +2498,12 @@ static void pulse_retarget_dualsense_mono_streams(const char *preferred)
 {
     struct pulse_stream *stream, *next;
 
+    if (preferred)
+        TRACE("Forcing DualSense mono streams to newly-added speaker %s.\n", debugstr_a(preferred));
+
     LIST_FOR_EACH_ENTRY_SAFE(stream, next, &dualsense_mono_streams, struct pulse_stream, dualsense_mono_entry)
     {
-        if (stream->dualsense_mono_hotplug_generation == g_dualsense_mono_speaker_add_generation
+        if (!preferred && stream->dualsense_mono_hotplug_generation == g_dualsense_mono_speaker_add_generation
                 && stream->haptic_hotplug_generation == g_haptic_hotplug_generation
                 && pulse_stream_ready(stream))
             continue;
